overview: The user wanted to significantly improve the aesthetics of their sleep
  questionnaire app, which they felt was too generic. The agent initiated a
  comprehensive redesign, starting with a new calming, sleep-themed color
  palette using OKLCH values and custom CSS utility classes. Key areas of focus
  included the main form layout, the welcome (intro) section, and all individual
  questionnaire sections, which were updated with consistent card-style
  groupings, improved typography, and interactive states for form elements. The
  report section also received a major overhaul to ensure consistent themed
  gradients for card headers and proper use of theme-based colors for text and
  backgrounds. Additionally, a console error related to  values being
  passed to input components was identified and fixed. The agent iteratively
  refined the styling, addressing inconsistencies and incorporating user
  feedback, resulting in a polished, cohesive, and professional-looking
  application.
